Cheers! An exceptionally moving and brilliantly acted human drama featuring a cast of the screen' s creme de la creme. Young pre.  Titanic. Leo di. Caprio is electrifying stealing scenes with aplomb from. De. Niro and. Streep. The great. Diane. Keaton is heart breaking as the tragic. Bessie whose generosity and kindness propels the drama. Broadway legend. Gwen. Verdon is a delightful scene stealer. A brilliant gem. Have a box of tissues handy. An unforgetable experience! Luv, diana

I just bought this DVD and open the package to play the DVD and the DVD was skipping. Was waiting for it to stop but it kept skipping parts so I got mad and took it out of my DVD player. It is sad that you pay for something only to find out the product does not work.
I like the movie but was not happy about the ending , so many questions.

This is my favorite movie of all time.  I ordered this edition to replace my original copy.  Just want to add that the description of the film on the back cover is inaccurate.  It states that Lee left behind Bessie to care for their father, Marvin, but that's not the case.  Lee left, but it was Bessie who stayed behind to care for their father.  Also, the front cover choice is somewhat confusing.  I see why they'd want to show a beach (given one of the scenes), but why show the four unknown people walking on it, who have nothing to do with the movie?
Brilliant acting. Diane Keaton plays aunt to Leo DiCaprio and sister to Streep. Hune Cronyn is the aged father. Classic drama circa 1996. No special features.
